label("$P$",(5,0),S);
label("5",(0,0)--(5,0),S);
label("10",(0,0)--(5,8.6603),NW);
[/asy]

Then $\triangle ABP$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle, so $AP=\sqrt{3}BP=5\sqrt{3}\text{ cm}.$ Thus, the height of the pile is $$5 + 5\sqrt{3} + 5 = \boxed{10 + 5\sqrt{3}}\text{ cm.}$$
#### 10 + 5\sqrt{3}

We begin by drawing a diagram: [asy]
pair A,B,C,D,X,Y,H;
A=(-12,12*sqrt(3)); D=(0,0); C=(12,12*sqrt(3)); B=(0,5+12*sqrt(3)); X=(B+C)/2; Y=(A+D)/2; H=(A+C)/2;
draw(A--B--C--D--cycle); draw(X--Y);

